\begin_layout Standard
\paragraph_spacing onehalf
I am glad to put some conclusive words in this document after taking the
 course.
 The most important, also the most fruitful part, are various teaching technique
s learned and observed.
 I have a few self-critiques on the two presentations I gave:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
\paragraph_spacing onehalf
The first one I prepared was about uniform convergence.
 What I learned from the feedback is that I shall keep in mind the range
 of suitable topics and the students' knowledge level.
 Uniform convergence is an essential topic in analysis, but it also requires
 to learn 
\begin_inset Formula $\epsilon$
\end_inset

-
\begin_inset Formula $\delta$
\end_inset

 language beforehand and it is hard to understand the importance without
 advancing to courses like real analysis.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
\paragraph_spacing onehalf
The second one was mainly on how to use calculus to explain how planimeter
 works.
 I like the topic quite much because it only uses very basic calculus and
 the integral is very straight forward.
 It could be better if I can find one and let the audience practice on themselve
s.
 What I am quite satisfied with is that I grabbed a squeegee from one of
 my officemates for illustration because it is much handier than a long
 ruler.
\end_layout

