\begin_layout Standard
\paragraph_spacing onehalf
On Nov.26 I observed one of Dr.
 Maxwell's M362K classes.
 I heard some of the practices he put on the classes beforehand, like moderate
 preview work and QOBBC (Questions-On-Board-Before-Class, I coined the abbreviat
ion :D).
 Surely these requirements will make students more or less learn on their
 own basis and lead to a better outcome.
 The two TAs also attended the class, assisting the instructor while also
 answering the students' questions and overseeing the in-class tasks.
 However, my partner is kind of a student with a slow reaction and he had
 few clues on most of the problems.
 I also consulted this issue with Dr.
 Nibert (since I am also TAing two M362K sections), and he shared some of
 his ideas in response: it might be worth more effort to make students in
 the middle-lower part get engaged and improved.
 I have included some of my ideas in the diversity and inclusivity statement
 but I need to try them out next semester to see if they can come into effect.
\end_layout

